<title type="html"><![CDATA[sound range, blip, 0..15, 0..127, 0.. 1.0  zero axis, center]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=4876&amp;p=43555#p43555"><![CDATA[
I see; yes, as long as you do output-=output&gt;&gt;N every output sample, and add <em>deltas</em> to the output, you'll get a high-pass. For the NES, N should be 8 or 9, as this gives an effective equivalent to approximately output*=0.9961 and output*=0.998, respectively. Note that these assume a sample rate of around 44 kHz.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=17">blargg</a> — Sat Feb 21, 2009 2:16 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
